</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cryptic species and phylogeography of alpine fairy shrimp in the Sierra Nevada Mountain Range-</strong> investigating species distributions and population genetic structure of alpine fairy shrimp (Branchinecta spp.) Collaborators: Roland Knapp, Christopher Rodgers, and Bernie May</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Conservation genetics of endangered vernal pool fairy shrimp-</strong> developing molecular markers and surveying population genetic structure for species recovery planning. Collaborators: Josh Hull and Bernie May</li>\r\n</ol>'),(1585,426,'__research_projects','field_530507efae298'),(1586,426,'_publications','<a title=\"Kristy Deiner Google Scholar Profile\" href=\"http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=KdbiEfsAAAAJ\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Google Scholar Profile</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Deiner, K.</strong>, Lemmon, A.R., Mack A., Fleischer R.C., Dumbacher, J.P. (2011) A passerine bird’s evolution corroborates the geologic history of the island of New Guinea. PLoS One 6(5): e19479.\r\n\r\nE. P. Dahlhoff, S.L. Fearnley, D. A. Bruce, A. G. Gibbs, R. Stoneking, D.M. McMillan, <strong>K. Deiner</strong>, J. T. Smiley, N. E. Rank (2008) Effects of temperature on physiology and reproductive success of a montane leaf beetle: implications for persistence of native populations enduring climate change. Physiological and Biochemical Zoology 81(6):718–732. Cited 15 times.\r\n\r\nDumbacher, J.P., <strong>K. Deiner</strong>, L. Thompson, R.C. Fleischer (2008) Phylogeny of the avian genus Pitohui and the evolution of toxicity in birds. Molecular phylogenetics and Evolution 49:774–781. Cited 13 times.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deiner, K.</strong>, Garza, J. C., Coey, R., Girman, D. J (2007) The effect of landscape features on the genetic structure of rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss) in the Russian River Watershed. Conservation Genetics 8(2): 437-454. Cited 26 times.'),(1587,426,'__publications','field_5305081a9bade'),(1588,430,'_edit_last','1'),(1589,430,'_edit_l