ogression between native golden trout and introduced rainbow trout. Mol. Ecol. Res. 9:339-343 (pdf).\r\n\r\n<strong>Earlier publications:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Publications 2005-2008\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/publications/publications-2005-2008/\">2005-2008</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Publications 2000-2004\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/publications/publications-2000-2004/\">2000-2004</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Publications 1993-1999\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/publications/publications-1993-1999/\">1993-1999</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Publications 1990-1992\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/publications/142-2/\">1990-1992</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Publications','','inherit','closed','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2014-03-03 19:08:58','2014-03-03 19:08:58','',12,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(288,1,'2014-03-05 19:36:21','2014-03-05 19:36:21','Our work at the Genomic Variation Laboratory (GVL) addresses important questions about the population genetics of threatened and endangered species. We use molecular tools such as microsatellites, single nucleotide polymorphisms, and high throughput sequencing to evaluate the processes that create and maintain biodiversity.\r\n\r\nExamples of current research <a title=\"Projects\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/projects/\" target=\"_blank\">projects</a> include: using molecular techniques to evaluate predation rates on Delta smelt, determining the genetic basis of disease resistance in rainbow trout, and investigating the ecology and evolution of various salmonid species. To address these pressing issues, we collaborate with numerous state and federal agencies, non-profits, and tribal organizations.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_239\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-239\" alt=\"$89,045 Kern Community Foundation Grant\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kern_community_foundation_grant.png\" width=\"240\" height=\"181\" /> $89,045 Kern Community Foundation Grant[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe GVL is also an active training ground for a large number of young <a title=\"People\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/people/\" target=\"_blank\">scientists</a> at various stages in their careers, from high school students to graduate students to project scientists.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_247\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"110\"]<a title=\"Support Us\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/support-us/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-247 \" alt=\"Learn About Our Projects\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_home_owl.png\" width=\"110\" height=\"83\" /></a> <a title=\"Projects\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/projects/\">Learn About Our Projects</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_246\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"110\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_home_catfish.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-246 \" alt=\"Support Us\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_home_catfish.png\" width=\"110\" height=\"83\" /></a> <a title=\"Support Us\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/support-us/\">Support Us</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_248\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"110\"]<a title=\"UC Davis Salmon Genetics Meeting 2012\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/Coastwide/2012_Coastwide_Salmonid_Genetics_Meeting/Home.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-248 \" alt=\"2012 Coastwide Salmon Genetics Meeting at UC Davis\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_home_salmon.png\" width=\"110\" height=\"83\" /></a> <a title=\"UC Davis Salmon Genetics Meeting 2012\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/Coastwide/2012_Coastwide_Salmonid_Genetics_Meeting/Home.html\" target=\"_blank\">2012 Coastwide Salmon Genetics Meeting at UC Davis</a>[/caption]','Home','','inherit','closed','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2014-03-05 19:36:21','2014-03-05 19:36:21','',30,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2014-03-05 19:38:15','2014-03-05 19:38:15','The Conservation Genetics Fund supports the Genomic Variation Laboratory (GVL) at UC Davis. Your donation supports both quality science that informs species conservation and the students that generate that science.\r\n\r\nThe Genomic Variation Laboratory works with wildlife managers to help answer questions essential for species conservation. For example, <a title=\"Projects\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/projects/\" target=\"_blank\">our work</a> helps define species and their phylogenetic relationships and informs the genetics of reintroductions. We study topics such as evolution, predation, aquaculture, population genetics structure, hybridization, and genetic management for reintroduction of salmonids.\r\n\r\nOur lab trains undergraduate and graduate <a title=\"People\" href=\"http://http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/people/\" target=\"_blank\">students</a> in many different molecular biological techniques, preparing them for a wide variety of careers. Bernie May is very supportive of career development and encourages his students to attend conferences, participate in internships, and network with agency biologists. We also host visiting researchers from outside the university to work with us in our lab.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_239\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"240\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-239\" alt=\"$89,045 Kern Community Foundation Grant\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kern_community_foundation_grant.png\" width=\"240\" height=\"181\" /> $89,045 Kern Community Foundation Grant[/caption]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Ways to Make a Donation:</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Online: Donate through the secure UC Davis donation website <a title=\"Giving to UC Davis\" href=\"https://awc.ucdavis.edu/MakeAGift.aspx?alloccat=130202120\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>By Mail: Mail your check made out to “University of California Regents” to Bernie May, Meyer Hall, 1 Shields Avenue, Davis, CA 95616. Please <a title=\"E-Mail Bernie May\" href=\"mailto:bpmay@ucdavis.edu?subject=Mail%20Donation\">email Bernie May</a> to let him know the check is coming.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn more about making a donation: Contact Dr. Bernie May through <a title=\"E-Mail Bernie May\" href=\"mailto:bpmay@ucdavis.edu?subject=Mail%20Donation\">email</a> or phone (530) 754-8123</li>\r\n</ol>','Support Us','','inherit','closed','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2014-03-05 19:38:15','2014-03-05 19:38:15','',14,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(290,1,'2014-03-05 19:38:43','2014-03-05 19:38:43','<strong>From Sac. Metro Airport:</strong>\r\n\r\nGet on I-5 south from airport Blvd.\r\n\r\nTake I-80 West towards San Francisco.\r\n\r\n<strong>From I-80 east or west:</strong>\r\n\r\nExit at the \"U.C. Davis/Old Davis Road\" exit and travel North.\r\n\r\nFollow Old Davis Road and go straight through first stop sign.\r\n\r\nCross bridge and turn left at first intersection, La Rue\r\n\r\nTurn right on Bioletti Way, and left in the parking lot. There is a permit dispenser just as you enter from this side. Parking is $7 per day.\r\n\r\nMeyer Hall is on the corner of Bioletti and La Rue.\r\n\r\nThe GVL is on the second floor in Rm. 2403 in the north building of Meyer Hall.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-231 aligncenter\" style=\"font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1;\" alt=\"gvl_map_freeway\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_map_freeway.jpg\" width=\"604\" height=\"455\" /><img class=\"size-full wp-image-232 aligncenter\" alt=\"gvl_map_meyer_hall\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvl_map_meyer_hall.jpg\" width=\"558\" height=\"497\" /></p>','Directions','','inherit','closed','open','','230-revision-v1','','','2014-03-05 19:38:43','2014-03-05 19:38:43','',230,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/230-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(291,1,'2014-03-05 19:40:15','2014-03-05 19:40:15','The Conservation Genetics Fund supports the Genomic Variation Laboratory (GVL) at UC Davis. Your donation supports both quality science that informs species conservation and the students that generate that science.\r\n\r\nThe Genomic Variation Laboratory works with wildlife managers to help answer questions essential for species conservation. For example, <a title=\"Projects\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/projects/\" target=\"_blank\">our work</a> helps define species and their phylogenetic relationships and informs the genetics of reintroductions. We study topics such as evolution, predation, aquaculture, population genetics structure, hybridization, and genetic management for reintroduction of salmonids.\r\n\r\nOur lab trains undergraduate and graduate <a title=\"People\" href=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/people/\" target=\"_blank\">students</a> in many different molecular biological techniques, preparing them for a wide variety of careers. Bernie May is very supportive of career development and encourages his students to attend conferences, participate in internships, and network with agency biologists. We also host visiting researchers from outside the university to work with us in our lab.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_239\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"240\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-239\" alt=\"$89,045 Kern Community Foundation Grant\" src=\"http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/kern_community_foundation_grant.png\" width=\"240\" height=\"181\" /> $89,045 Kern Community Found