IGM EP1 PROTOCOL.doc\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/gvl/Conservation_Genetics_Fund/Protocols_files/FLUIDIGM%20EP1%20PROTOCOL.doc\">Fluidigm EP1 Protocol</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Illumina</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Protocols_files/RAD-SEQ Protocol.doc\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/gvl/Conservation_Genetics_Fund/Protocols_files/RAD-SEQ%20Protocol.doc\">RAD-SEQ Protocol</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Other</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Protocols_files/tissuesampleprot.pdf\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/gvl/Conservation_Genetics_Fund/Protocols_files/tissuesampleprot.pdf\">Tissue Sampling</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Supplies.html\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/gvl/Conservation_Genetics_Fund/Supplies.html\">Ordering and Receiving Supplies</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Supplies.html\" href=\"http://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/gvl/Conservation_Genetics_Fund/Supplies.html\">PCR Tips and Tricks</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Protocols and Procedures','','inherit','closed','open','','217-revision-v1','','','2014-03-07 20:59:43','2014-03-07 20:59:43','',217,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/217-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2014-03-07 21:02:06','2014-03-07 21:02:06','<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Dilution of Gel Company Fluorescein Ladder : 50 to 400 bp for Manual Acrylamide Gels</span></h3>\r\nGel Company Ladder Catalog Number: MFK400-MD\r\n\r\nTo make 350 ul total (aliquotted into 10 small tubes):\r\n\r\nIn a tube, add\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>30 ul H<sub>2</sub>O</li>\r\n	<li>10 ul ladder</li>\r\n	<li>300 ul</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMix and aliquot into 10 small tubes\r\n\r\nThis dilution is adequate to be visible without agarose-overlay staining when loading 1 ul of diluted ladder to a well. If you are going to use an agarose-overlay, you can dilute this dilution 1:1 with more loading dye.','Gelco Fluorescein Ladder','','publish','closed','open','','gelco-fluorescein-ladder','','','2014-03-07 21:19:06','2014-03-07 21:19:06','',217,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/?page_id=312',0,'page','',0),(313,1,'2014-03-07 21:02:06','2014-03-07 21:02:06','<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Dilution of Gel Company Fluorescein Ladder : 50 to 400 bp for Manual Acrylamide Gels</span></h3>\r\nGel Company Ladder Catalog Number: MFK400-MD\r\n\r\nTo make 350 ul total (aliquotted into 10 small tubes):\r\n\r\nIn a tube, add\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>30 ul H2O</li>\r\n	<li>10 ul ladder</li>\r\n	<li>300 ul</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMix and aliquot into 10 small tubes\r\n\r\nThis dilution is adequate to be visible without agarose-overlay staining when loading 1 ul of diluted ladder to a well. If you are going to use an agarose-overlay, you can dilute this dilution 1:1 with more loading dye.','Gelco Fluorescein Ladder','','inherit','closed','open','','312-revision-v1','','','2014-03-07 21:02:06','2014-03-07 21:02:06','',312,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/312-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2014-03-07 21:02:51','2014-03-07 21:02:51','<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">0.05ug/ul for agarose gels</span></h3>\r\n<strong>Amount:</strong>\r\n\r\nLadder stock (1ug/ul): 10ul\r\n\r\nLoading dye (BPB/XC found in fridge): 40ul\r\n\r\nNanopure water: 150ul\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This makes 200ul - aliquot into two tubes</li>\r\n	<li>Use 1ul in a typical agarose gel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Diluting 1Kb Plus Ladder with Dye','','inherit','closed','open','','309-revision-v1','','','2014-03-07 21:02:51','2014-03-07 21:02:51','',309,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/309-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(315,1,'2014-03-07 21:03:10','2014-03-07 21:03:10','<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>For denaturing polyacrylamide gels</strong></span></h3>\r\n<strong>Amounts:</strong>\r\n\r\nFormamide: 200 ml\r\n\r\nBromophenol Blue: 10 mg\r\n\r\nXylene Cyanol FF: 10 mg\r\n\r\nEDTA: 4 ml of 0.5 M pH 8.0 stock\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transfer into 50 mL conical tubes and store at -20º</li>\r\n	<li>When supply in 4º runs low, thaw one tube and add to 4º beaker</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','98% Formamide Loading Dye','','inherit','closed','open','','307-revision-v1','','','2014-03-07 21:03:10','2014-03-07 21:03:10','',307,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2014-03-07 21:07:00','2014-03-07 21:07:00','<strong>For 100ml of storage buffer:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50 ml Glycerol</li>\r\n	<li>1 ml 1M Tris-HCl pH 7.5</li>\r\n	<li>0.29g CaCl<sub>2</sub></li>\r\n	<li>ddH20 to 100ml</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For 10 ml of Proteinase K stock solution:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Put 10ml of storage buffer in a 15ml screw-cap tube</li>\r\n	<li>Add 100mg of Proteinase K</li>\r\n	<li>Mix well by inverting until crystals are dissolved</li>\r\n	<li>Put 1ml aliquots into 1.5ml microfuge tubes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nStore at -20°C','Proteinase K','','publish','closed','open','','proteinase-k','','','2014-03-07 21:19:41','2014-03-07 21:19:41','',217,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/?page_id=316',0,'page','',0),(317,1,'2014-03-07 21:07:00','2014-03-07 21:07:00','<strong>For 100ml of storage buffer:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>50 ml Glycerol</li>\r\n	<li>1 ml 1M Tris-HCl pH 7.5</li>\r\n	<li>0.29g CaCl2</li>\r\n	<li>ddH20 to 100ml</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For 10 ml of Proteinase K stock solution:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Put 10ml of storage buffer in a 15ml screw-cap tube</li>\r\n	<li>Add 100mg of Proteinase K</li>\r\n	<li>Mix well by inverting until crystals are dissolved</li>\r\n	<li>Put 1ml aliquots into 1.5ml microfuge tubes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nStore at -20°C','Proteinase K','','inherit','closed','open','','316-revision-v1','','','2014-03-07 21:07:00','2014-03-07 21:07:00','',316,'http://localhost/~psalessi/Genetics_Lab/316-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2014-03-07 21:08:00','2014-03-07 21:08:00','<strong>Buffers &amp; Stocks</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"98% Formamide Loading